sdSize

public static void sdSize(String sdSize,
                          String message)
                   throws AndroidContainerConfigurationException
Checks if user set size of SD card in the proper format. SD card size has to be between 9M (9126K) and 1023G. Everything out of this range is considered to be invalid. This method follows size and format recommendation of mksdcard tool from the Android tools distribution.

Parameters:
sdSize - size of sd card
message - The exception message
Throws:
AndroidContainerConfigurationException - when sdSize is invalid

isConsolePortValid

public static void isConsolePortValid(String consolePort)
                               throws AndroidContainerConfigurationException
Checks if console port is in valid range. Console port has to be even number in range 5554L - 5584L.

Parameters:
consolePort - console port to check validity of
Throws:
AndroidContainerConfigurationException - if console port is null or not a number or not valid

isAdbPortValid

public static void isAdbPortValid(String adbPort)
                           throws AndroidContainerConfigurationException
Checks if adb port is in valid range. adbPort port has to be odd number in range 5555L - 5585L

Parameters:
adbPort - adb port to check validity of
Throws:
AndroidContainerConfigurationException - if adb port is null or not a number or not valid
